      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Critics argue that substantive due process has been misused to impose liberal values and social justice on the Constitution, often disregarding the original intent of the Founding Fathers. They claim that this approach undermines the rule of law and allows the judiciary to impose its own moral agenda, rather than strictly interpreting the Constitution. In contrast, procedural due process advocates argue that the Constitution should only protect fundamental rights through explicit text or clear historical precedent, rather than relying on judicial activism and subjective interpretations.",
